There are 8 subsets total (2³ = 8).

(a) {1, 2, 3} ⊕ {3, 4, 5}
Elements in first only: {1, 2}
Elements in second only: {4, 5}
Union: {1, 2, 4, 5}

(b) Proof:
x ∈ A ⊕ B 
⟺ (x ∈ A ∨ x ∈ B) ∧ ¬(x ∈ A ∧ x ∈ B)  [Def of XOR]
⟺ (x ∈ A ∧ x ∉ B) ∨ (x ∈ B ∧ x ∉ A)   [Logical equivalence]
⟺ x ∈ (A - B) ∨ x ∈ (B - A)           [Def of Set Difference]
⟺ x ∈ (A - B) ∪ (B - A)               [Def of Union]

